      "text": [
        ": \"إِنَّمَا اسْتَحْسَنُوا إِشْعَارَ الْبُدْنِ لِأَنَّ أَوَّلَ قَطْرَةٍ تَقْطُرُ مِنْ دَمِهَا يَغْفِرُ اللَّهُ عَزَّ وَجَلَّ لَهُ عَلَى ذَلِكَ.\""
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2570 - Amr ibn Shumr narrated from Jabir, from Abu Ja'far (as), who said:\n\"They deemed the marking of the sacrificial animals commendable because with the first drop of its blood that falls, Allah (swt), the Almighty, forgives the one offering it.\""
        ]
